Anonymous Wed 31 Jul 2024 03:27:36 No.67857242 Report
Quoted By: >>67857588
>>67856891
last thread there were 3 different types of animation posted.
1. PrincessSnuSnu's Lena animations use tweening and simple translation like a rig. The pros are that it can be done fairly quickly especially with pixel art. The downside is that it is stiffer and more limiting. They are my favorites.
2. CMT's Amelie animations are hand drawn and colored. The upside to this animation is that it is liberating and you can do whatever you want. Downside is that it takes the longest and only professionals can make it look good.
3. Slamanon's Doberella animation is 3D. Upside is that once you have a model it is much easier to animate than 2D for most things. Downside is that you still have to make the model and it is much less intuitive than animating in 2D. Hope you like blender.
